{
  "stem": "18102.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we know the history of that period of time with Japan, and the Germans being allies, that that was not the thing to do, to issue visas, particularly to Jews who were escaping their fate.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so the, the only motivation that Sugihara could have possibly had was one of humanitarian spirit, devotion to justice, and, I guess, a, a sympathy to the plight of people who were caught and would be suffering simply because they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I don't think it's unusual for the Japanese.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I don't believe that the Japanese, as a people, are, are different than that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I have found-- of course, now I, I know many Japanese.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm friends with many Japanese and have discussed this with many.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I have found that this quality of a sympathy, of a, of a basic understanding of human rights, as it were, is not uncommon in Japan.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sugihara found himself in a position where he could do something, as he said, to carry out the dictates of his god rather than the dictates of his country, officially, of his government, and did.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But most Japanese that I've run into, at least from what I've been able to see, understood and understand today the plight of the Jews, and the sufferings that were committed to them only because they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, actually, it has because, as you probably know, I am a director of the United States Holocaust Memorial Museum in Washington DC.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did that with the express reason that I felt it was my obligation to make sure that this story-- not just the Sugihara story, of course-- but that the memory of the Holocaust was maintained, so that it would prevent it from occurring again.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
